Package: DRMLSurv
Title: Doubly Robust ML and Matching for Two-Stage Survival Outcomes
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Eric", "Anto", , "eric.anto@utah.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements a two-stage survival analysis pipeline that combines
    (i) imputation of censored stage-specific survival times via donor matching,
    (ii) construction of matched counterfactual outcomes under static and dynamic
    treatment regimes, and (iii) estimation of optimal dynamic treatment rules
    using machine learning and cross-fitting. The toolkit supports nearest and
    full matching, optional exact matching, balance diagnostics, and flexible
    censoring/propensity score models via DoubleScore/SuperLearner-style
    learners.
